      answer:
        '<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"><span>1. What is Acute Psychiatric care?</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Acute psychiatric care involves </span><a href="https://sukoonhealth.com/psychiatric-services/acute-psychiatry-care/"><span>Inpatient</span></a><span> hospitalization with high levels of personalized care, comfort, and safety to meet the needs of individuals who have emotional and behavioral difficulties.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"> </p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>2. What is the need for psychiatric care?</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Understanding, managing and supporting the bio-psycho-social needs of the person experiencing distress requires expertise and skill. The multidisciplinary </span><a href="https://sukoonhealth.com/our-doctors/"><span>team</span></a><span> adept at understanding the human mind and behavior treat the person with respect and dignity to help them integrate back into their daily lives as a better version of themselves. </span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"> </p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>3. </span><span>What kind of patients require acute psychiatric care?</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Acute </span><a href="https://sukoonhealth.com/mental-health-consultation/psychiatric-treatment-in-India/"><span>psychiatric</span></a><span> care is provided to individuals who find themselves in crisis; are violent/aggressive and a threat to others and themselves and are unable to take care of oneself are recommended to seek acute psychiatric care. </span></p>\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"> </p>\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"><span>4. What is the duration of the treatment program?</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Duration can last anywhere from one or two days to several weeks. The length of a hospital stay is determined by several factors: </span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>â€¢ Severity of illness </span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>â€¢ Patientâ€™s participation in treatment and insight into his or her condition </span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>â€¢ Patientâ€™s mental status and improvement since admission </span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>â€¢ Situation into which the patient is being discharged</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>In other words, whether the patient will have a supportive environment with appropriate outpatient treatment after leaving the hospital.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"> </p>\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"><span>5. What mental health issues are targeted in acute psychiatric care?</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Individuals suffering from anxiety, depression, substance use, psychosis, obsessive compulsive disorder, bipolar affective disorder, traumatic experiences, self harm or suicidal behaviour and various other mental health issues are targeted in acute psychiatric care.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"> </p>\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"><span>6. Are the family members allowed to stay or meet the patient?</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>As per hospital protocols, we do not think it is compulsory for family members to stay with the patient. However anyone wishing to stay will be facilitated in a manner in which it doesnâ€™t interfere with treatment and well being of the patient. In our experience we have found that recovery is best when there is minimal emotional stimulation and distraction.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"> </p>\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"><span>7. Is it curable?</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>The human mind is adaptable. While some mental health concerns are not entirely curable, they can be learnt to manage better with the support and expertise of the clinical </span><a href="https://sukoonhealth.com/our-doctors/"><span>team</span></a><span>. The end aim of care is to support independent care and contribute to society with their unique skill set. </span></p>\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"> </p>\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"><span>8. What basic facilities are provided to the patient?</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>The </span><a href="https://sukoonhealth.com/psychiatric-hospital-in-Gurgaon/"><span>facility</span></a><span> provides a fully furnished room with double bed setting, a couch, television with OTT platforms, an air conditioner with both cold and hot temperature settings, wifi access, mini fridge, five meals a day, fully functioning bathroom with hot water at all times, balcony and terrace access.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"> </p>\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"><span>9. Does the facility provide any 24*7 attendants in the facility?</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>The facility is designed keeping in mind the needs of the patient ranging from nursing station on each floor to person specific nursing and general duty assistants who are available 24*7. </span></p>\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"> </p>\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"><span>10. Are there any medical health services provided by the hospital?</span></p>\n<p>Our facility is primarily dedicated to the mental health services, however, other medical health services are provided by the hospital keeping the individual\'s need - the center either seeks to liaison with the medical experts in the field and other hospitals like <a href="https://www.medanta.org/">Medanta</a> and  The services include consults for cardiology, gastroenterology, dermatology etc.</p>',
