      answer:
        '<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"><span>1. What does women-focused care mean?</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>At Sukoon, we provide in-patient services focused specifically on the mental health needs of </span><a href="https://sukoonhealth.com/psychiatric-services/women-focused-care/"><span>women</span></a><span>. Our services focus on and are designed keeping in mind the specific needs of women with anxiety, depression and other mental health concerns. Often reproductive cycle changes, hormonal imbalances and life stressors can cause increased vulnerability to mental health conditions and emotional disturbances. </span></p>\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"> </p>\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"><span>2. Is it different from any other program?</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Our facility is equipped for specialized requirements of the women such as: crisis intervention unit made available specifically for women; 24*7 dedicated nurses; exclusive residential floor for </span><a href="https://sukoonhealth.com/psychiatric-services/acute-psychiatry-care/"><span>inpatient</span></a><span> treatment for women; floor access to female-only staff of nurses and attendants.  </span></p>\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"> </p>\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"><span>3</span><span>. Are there any illnesses that are specific to women? </span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Yes, there are psychiatric conditions that may develop during pregnancy and postpartum such as depression, psychosis, etc, stress and trauma related to infertility or pregnancy loss, premenstrual mood difficulties, emotional changes and other psychiatric symptoms due to transition to menopause.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"> </p>\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"><span>4. Are children allowed to stay with a female patient?</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>No, children arenâ€™t allowed to stay with female patients. However, meetings can be arranged under supervision after assessing an individual\'s current mental health and suggestions of the clinical </span><a href="https://sukoonhealth.com/our-doctors/"><span>team</span></a><span>. In our experience we have found that recovery is best when there is minimal emotional stimulation and distraction.</span></p>',
