      answer:
        '<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"><span>1. Can I order food from outside? </span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Yes, we can order food for the individual from outside. The food should be sealed. The food can be ordered after consultation from the dietician at Sukoon to avoid any health related complications. </span><span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"> </p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>2. Can I get my play station?</span><span><br></span><span><br></span><span>Yes, the individual can get his/her play station. He/she can use the playstation post his sessions during his/her free time so that he/she stays in touch with their old life. Enjoying your stay at Sukoon is our priority. We believe using external aids like play station can act as a catalyst and help them with the same. </span><span><br></span><span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"> </p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>3. How will I pass my time during my stay?</span><span><br></span><span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>The days of the individual are highly structured and time bound. These are planned by keeping the current symptoms in mind and to improve quality of life. Another aim is to teach new coping skills through the introduction of various sessions including psychotherapy, art therapy, mental gym, physiotherapy as well as yoga. </span><span><br></span><span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"> </p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>4. How can I stay physically active during my stay at Sukoon?</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>At Sukoon, we have a functional gym which can help you in adopting physical workout to enhance their health. The gym accessories can be modified as per your preference and needs. Physiotherapists can also help in designing a workout schedule for the same. We also have services like table tennis as well as badminton to increase everyday activity and to bring variety to modes of physical workout. </span><span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"> </p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>5. Do I have to do art therapy?</span><span><br></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><a href="https://sukoonhealth.com/mental-health-consultation/art-therapy-for-mental-health/"><span>Art</span></a><span> therapy helps in enhancing the modalities being focused upon in psychotherapy. It opens a road to the expression of conflicted thoughts and emotions. This can aid the process of therapy as sometimes it gets difficult for the individual to express through talking. Here at </span><a href="https://sukoonhealth.com/"><span>Sukoon</span></a><span>, we have a glass art studio which has been designated for art therapy. We can employ movement therapy, drum circle as well as activities using different art material. </span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"> </p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>6. What is a mental gym session?</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Mental Gym sessions are done basically to stimulate cognitive processes. Exercises such as reading, solving puzzles, word search , sudoku, mazes and concentration grid are also given to build, focus, attention and enhance problem solving skills.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"> </p>\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"><span>7. Can I tend to my work while I stay at Sukoon?</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Yes, if one is not symptomatic and work doesnâ€™t interfere in the treatment process they can tend to do their work while they stay at Sukoon, however it is advisable to minimize the external stimulus during the stay as it may interfere with the recovery process. In case the clinical team approves of working then the sessions are planned accordingly to accommodate the work. </span></p>\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"> </p>\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"><span>8. Can I go out to spend some time with my family?</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>The family can visit the client on a regular basis once the symptomatology settles and  the clinical team approves. The treatment plan also includes short visits where the individual is allowed to go out with family and spend some quality time with them.  </span></p>\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"> </p>\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"><span>9. Can my family stay with me during the hospitalization?</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>The family can stay with the client during their hospitalization once the symptomatology settles and  the clinical </span><a href="https://sukoonhealth.com/our-doctors/"><span>team</span></a><span> approves. In our experience we have found that recovery is best when there is minimal emotional stimulation and distraction when the person is symptomatic.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"> </p>\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"><span>10. Can my friends visit me during my stay at Sukoon? </span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Yes, the friends can visit the individual during his/her stay. The meeting can be scheduled after a discussion with the clinical team  and the family members. It is generally advised for the friends to meet the individual after there is improvement in the presenting symptoms. We at Sukoon believe that meeting friends and family can act as a motivating factor and can increase the pace of recovery.</span></p>',
